{
  "text": "WT-1 is a transcription factor that was originally described as a tumour suppressor gene but is now known to be involved in tumourigenesis. It can positively or negatively regulate the expression of various genes involved in cellular proliferation, differentiation and apoptosis (L. [CITATION_1] . In normal adult tissue, WT-1 is expressed at low levels on haematopoietic stem cells, myoepithelial progenitor cells, renal podocytes and some cells in the testis and ovary [CITATION_2] . It is known to be upregulated in epithelioid MM but not in the sarcomatoid subtype and furthermore, its expression does not appear to be of significant prognostic value [CITATION_3] . However, WT-1 is a relevant immune target in MM [CITATION_4] .",
  "correct_citation": {
